
[1]insidious

   INSID'IOUS, a. [L. insidiosus, from insideo, to lie in wait; in and
   sedeo, to sit.]

   1. Properly, lying in wait; hence, watching an opportunity to insnare
   or entrap; deceitful; sly; treacherous; used of persons.

   2. Intended to entrap; as insidious arts.
